  "notes": [
    "The taxonomy is intentionally compact (~45 roles) to stay within the 30–80 constraint while covering the highest-leverage functions for look replication.",
    "Cheek and brow functions are represented minimally (blush + contour/bronzer/highlighter) and can be expanded later via additive roles if technique cards require more specificity.",
    "Tool roles are a minimal cross-area set focused on high-frequency mapping and easy SKU matching; adding niche brush variants is deferred to avoid over-expansion.",
    "Synonyms are written to support SKU title parsing and user query normalization; market-specific synonym extensions can be layered later without changing any role_id."
  ],
